---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';

const team = [
  { title: 'Physicians on duty', text: 'A doctor is on duty throughout clinic hours — watching over each treatment, ready to adjust the prescription or respond the moment anything changes.' },
  { title: 'Renal dietitians', text: 'Our dietitians build a kidney-friendly plan around real Filipino food and your own preferences. Practical guidance you can actually live with, not a lecture.' },
  { title: 'Social workers', text: 'Dialysis brings worries beyond the medical. Our social workers help you navigate PhilHealth, costs and the paperwork, so you can focus on getting better.' },
  { title: 'Diagnostics & laboratory', text: 'We coordinate the bloodwork and diagnostics dialysis patients need with reputable, well-known partner laboratories — reliable results, on time, without the extra runaround.' },
];
---
<BaseLayout title="Services" description="Hemodialysis and a full range of modalities, wrap-around clinical support, and the quiet safety work behind every session at St. John Biocare." image="/images/og/og-services.jpg">
  <PageHero
    image="/images/photos/dsc_0038.webp"
    alt="A St. John Biocare dialysis treatment area with monitoring equipment"
    eyebrow="Services"
    title="Everything your dialysis care needs."
    subtitle="The clinical care, the people around your chair, and the safety work behind every session — explained plainly."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container stack" style="max-width:760px">
      <p class="lead">Good dialysis is rarely one thing done well. It is a hundred small things done
      right — session after session, year after year. After more than fifteen years caring for Filipinos
      with kidney disease, we have built our centers around that idea. What follows is what your care
      includes, and the standards behind it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--mist">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
      <p class="eyebrow">The treatment</p>
      <h2>Hemodialysis, matched to you.</h2>
      <p>At the center of everything we do is hemodialysis — modern machines, careful monitoring, strict
      infection control, and early-morning schedules built around patients and caregivers who still have
      work and family to get to. But no two patients are the same, and neither is the right treatment.</p>
      <p>So we offer a full range of modalities and choose with you: <strong>low-flux</strong> and
      <strong>high-flux hemodialysis</strong>, <strong>hemodiafiltration (HDF)</strong> at select branches
      for more thorough clearance, <strong>SLED (sustained low-efficiency dialysis)</strong> for patients
      who need a gentler, slower session, and <strong>isolated ultrafiltration (UF)</strong> when the goal
      is simply to remove excess fluid. The prescription is a clinical decision, revisited as your needs
      change — not a fixed setting.</p>

      <figure style="margin:22px 0 0">
        <img src="/images/photos/dsc_0033.webp"
             alt="A dialyzer on a hemodialysis machine during a treatment session" loading="lazy"
             style="max-width:300px;width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;display:block" width="1328" height="2000" />
        <figcaption class="muted" style="font-size:.82rem;margin-top:6px">A dialyzer at work during a session — where your blood is gently cleaned.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
      <p class="eyebrow">The team around your chair</p>
      <h2>A team, not just a machine.</h2>
      <p>A dialysis machine is only as good as the people watching over it. That is why your care here is
      wrapped in a whole team — and why we take the time to explain kidney health in plain language, so you
      and your family understand what is happening and what to do next. When you understand your treatment,
      you become part of it.</p>

      <div class="grid grid--2" style="margin-top:22px">
        {team.map((m) => (
          <div class="card">
            <h3 style="font-size:1.15rem">{m.title}</h3>
            <p style="margin:0">{m.text}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--mist">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
      <p class="eyebrow">Quality &amp; safety</p>
      <h2>The safety work you don't always see.</h2>
      <p>Much of what keeps dialysis safe happens quietly, between your sessions and behind the scenes.
      These are the standards we hold ourselves to, without being asked and without cutting corners.</p>

      <div class="grid grid--2" style="margin-top:22px">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="font-size:1.15rem">Innovator-brand medicines</h3>
          <p style="margin:0">We use well-established, proven <strong>innovator (original-brand)</strong>
          pharmaceutical products — the original manufacturers' own, not substitutes — for your
          erythropoietin, intravenous iron and <strong>halal-certified heparin</strong>, and for all our
          materials and chemicals.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="font-size:1.15rem">Trusted machines, maker-calibrated</h3>
          <p style="margin:0">Every center runs hemodialysis machines from <strong>well-known, established
          brands — locally and internationally</strong>, calibrated regularly by their
          <strong>original manufacturers</strong>, so the equipment caring for you performs exactly as it
          should.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="font-size:1.15rem">Dual-pass RO water, in every center</h3>
          <p style="margin:0">The water used in dialysis has to be exceptionally pure. Every center's
          treatment system uses a <strong>dual-pass reverse-osmosis (RO)</strong> setup — the water is
          purified twice before it ever reaches a machine — so high water-quality standards are met
          across the network.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="font-size:1.15rem">Dialyzer reprocessing &amp; infection control</h3>
          <p style="margin:0">Careful, protocol-driven dialyzer reprocessing and formal infection-control
          practices govern every session — the disciplined, unglamorous work that quietly keeps you
          safe.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="font-size:1.15rem">Closed Sundays — the work never stops</h3>
          <p style="margin:0">We close to patients on <strong>Sundays</strong>, and that is precisely when
          the deeper work happens: <strong>wall-to-wall clinic disinfection</strong> and full servicing of
          the <strong>water treatment system</strong> — disinfection, calibration, resetting and
          maintenance. You return to a center cleaned and checked from top to bottom.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--sand" style="padding-block:44px">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:920px">
      <figure style="margin:0">
        <picture>
          <source srcset="/images/og/og-services.webp" type="image/webp" />
          <img src="/images/og/og-services.jpg" width="1200" height="630" loading="lazy"
               alt="St. John Biocare services at a glance: hemodialysis, physicians on duty, renal dietitians, and social workers."
               style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:14px;box-shadow:var(--shadow)" />
        </picture>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
